{
  "stem": "21626.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was purely hoping that we wouldn't be persecuted if it came to persecution.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, lots of Jewish families did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was a purely a safeguard.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I could not make my English families understand this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They felt it meant that my parents wanted me to carry on being educated in, in a Christian way.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And as-- when I was with them, I went to a Methodist church.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I went to a Methodist Sunday school, and the same when I was with Auntie Marjorie.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They, being my guardians, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] when they had to fill in a form, you see, put me down as a, as a Methodist, of Church of Czechoslovakia, which was of that group.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And though I protested, the, the school felt, as I was in the care of the Rainfords, they had to abide by their wishes.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But though I didn't-- we had a rabbi at school, and he considered me one of his.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I-- well, I mean, to me it didn't matter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were all refugees.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I didn't, as such, go to many religious classes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And-- but I, I didn't have Jewish instruction.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I really didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You had very little Jewish instruction in my life, you know, because of this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But I never considered myself anything but a Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But of course, at the age of 12 or 13, you can't dictate, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you, you can't dictate into which group you should go.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And obviously, my guardian, guardians' wishes had to be adhered to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my sister was in a Church of England school, boarding school, a very posh school.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
